All Implemented Interfaces:
BoundedMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>
public abstract class ForwardingBoundedMap<K,V>
extends ForwardingMap<K,V>
implements BoundedMap<K,V>

A BoundedMap which forwards all its method calls to another BoundedMap. Subclasses should override one or more methods to modify the behavior of the backing map as desired per the decorator pattern.

Author:
Zhenya Leonov

offer

public boolean offer(K key,
                     V value)
Description copied from interface: BoundedMap
Associates the specified value with the specified key in this map if it is possible to do so immediately without violating capacity restrictions. If the map previously contained a mapping for the key, the old value is replaced by the specified value. This method is generally preferable to put(K, V), which can fail only by throwing an exception.

Specified by:
offer in interface BoundedMap<K,V>
Parameters:
key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
value - value to be associated with the specified key
Returns:
true if the entry was stored in this map, else false
